description.narrative: A total of 226,501 community members (89,571 women, 38,043 girls, 28,532 boys and 70,355 men) were reached through community dialogue to prevent child marriage, violence against children and women, and female genital mutilation. An evaluation of two of the 11 sites indicates a decline of perceptions supporting child marriage and FGM. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
